TY  - JOUR
T1  - Chutes Versus Ladders: Anchoring Events and a Punctuated-Equilibrium Perspective on Social Exchange Relationships
AU  - Ballinger, Gary A.
AU  - Rockmann, Kevin W.
Y1  - 2010/07/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.35.3.zok373
DO  - 10.5465/amr.35.3.zok373
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 373
EP  - 391
VL  - 35
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We integrate concepts from research on emotion and memory to show how critical exchanges?or anchoring events?can suddenly and durably change the rules for organizational relationships, leading them to reach nonreciprocal forms like altruism or competition. We define these events and discuss the likelihood of their occurring as a function of the current state of the relationship, the time in that state of the relationship, and the social context in which the event takes place.
AB  - We integrate concepts from research on emotion and memory to show how critical exchanges?or anchoring events?can suddenly and durably change the rules for organizational relationships, leading them to reach nonreciprocal forms like altruism or competition. We define these events and discuss the likelihood of their occurring as a function of the current state of the relationship, the time in that state of the relationship, and the social context in which the event takes place.
