TY  - JOUR
T1  - When Worlds Collide: The Internal Dynamics of Organizational Responses to Conflicting Institutional Demands
AU  - Pache, Anne-Claire
AU  - Santos, Filipe
Y1  - 2010/07/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.35.3.zok455
DO  - 10.5465/amr.35.3.zok455
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 455
EP  - 476
VL  - 35
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Organizations are increasingly subject to conflicting demands imposed by their institutional environments. This makes compliance impossible to achieve, because satisfying some demands requires defying others. Prior work simply suggests that organizations develop strategic responses in such situations. Our key contribution is to provide a more precise model of organizational responses that takes into account intraorganizational political processes. As a result, we identify situations in which conflicting institutional demands may lead to organizational paralysis or breakup.
AB  - Organizations are increasingly subject to conflicting demands imposed by their institutional environments. This makes compliance impossible to achieve, because satisfying some demands requires defying others. Prior work simply suggests that organizations develop strategic responses in such situations. Our key contribution is to provide a more precise model of organizational responses that takes into account intraorganizational political processes. As a result, we identify situations in which conflicting institutional demands may lead to organizational paralysis or breakup.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.35.3.zok455
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.35.3.zok455
Y2  - 2026/04/24
