TY  - JOUR
T1  - What About the Leader in Leader-Member Exchange? The Impact of Resource Exchanges and Substitutability on the Leader
AU  - Wilson, Kelly Schwind
AU  - Sin, Hock-peng
AU  - Conlon, Donald E.
Y1  - 2010/07/01
PY  - 2010
DA  - 2010/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.35.3.zok358
DO  - 10.5465/amr.35.3.zok358
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 358
EP  - 372
VL  - 35
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - To date, leader-member exchange (LMX) research has primarily examined member outcomes, such as member attitudes and performance. However, little research exists regarding outcomes specific to the leader. Focusing on the leader-member dyad, we develop a framework of leader outcomes resulting from resource exchanges with members. We propose specific resource substitutes and discuss the impact of LMX quality on the leader.
AB  - To date, leader-member exchange (LMX) research has primarily examined member outcomes, such as member attitudes and performance. However, little research exists regarding outcomes specific to the leader. Focusing on the leader-member dyad, we develop a framework of leader outcomes resulting from resource exchanges with members. We propose specific resource substitutes and discuss the impact of LMX quality on the leader.
